title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1977-06-09
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step, Jack Straw, They Love Each Other, Cassidy, Sunrise, Deal, Looks Like Rain, Loser, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Funiculi Funicula, Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Estimated Prophet-> Saint Stephen-> Not Fade Away-> Drums-> Saint Stephen-> Terrapin Station-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues, E: One More Saturday Night*

*Second Encore

reviews.review_text:
ANOTHER JOB WELL DONE EXTRA CRISPY!
                THANX CHARLIE

Outstanding Excellent recording. Thank You tremendously.
Really happy to see this show back up and with the best version.

One of the best? The last show of a magical tour.  Without a doubt.........
This is a GREAT show - one that is worthy of comparing to 5/7, 5/8, and 5/9.  However, this show does dot get that type of respect, in my opinion.  I believe this is an A+ show.
- Hawt! There are better shows, but not by much.

Five Star+ A great DEAL and the finest Music Never Stopped-absolutely brilliant. he singing of Bobby and Donna is spot on and a brilliant performance from everyone.Great Samson & delilah o through. Great sound as well. Having been listening to the May shows, I think that this is up there as one of the top three. I rate this wiith the DP 3 show May 22/77 and for me, the show of the 21/5/77,but it's all a matter of taste and, let's be honest,From April 77-the end of June they're all A- at the very worst. Thanks to Mr. Miller

best of the best Don't get me wrong, I love the matrixes as well. But no other recording of this show puts us in the presence of Jerry like this one. I actually usually prefer matrixes to soundboards--the latter usually leave me a little cold. I like the energy of audience recordings; they're more likely to bring all the magic back for me. But this recording in its present cleaned up shape is just phenomenal--you're so lost in the music (like you were at a show) that you don't even notice the absence of the audience. Which brings me to my point. Thank you, thank you, thank you Charlie. Truly, thank you. Like the Dead, you can't know how much joy you have brought to so many of us. Shout out to Duane as well--spectacular work here!
Just exactly perfect Another exceptional show from the just exactly perfect tour!!!

Man oh man!!! So, I am now 35 years old.... Crazy how time seems to have just up and fast forwarded 10 years! I was 12 in 1995, so this site has been my magical place. I have been to many shows, but no Jerry. I was in high school when I 1st learned about archive.org. I soon realized that one Mr. Charlie Miller always posted outstanding shows. I have been a dead head, as much as a guy can be with no Jerry, for 20 years now... Its because of this{1/2 step jam is playing, I'm in heaven) , its because of the people, keep the music very much alive!!! Thank you, and know that your work is very much appreciated. Great show!!
